learned from Mother Magpie how to build their nests, some one said, "We
ought to have a king. Oh, we need a king of the birds very much!" For
you see, already in the Garden of Birds trouble had begun. There were
disputes every morning as to which was the earliest bird who was
entitled to the worm. There were quarrels over the best places for
nest-building and over the fattest bug or beetle; and there was no one
